Study
3 ways to consume: env vars, command-line args, volume mount.
Size limit ~1 MiB.
Updates: env vars are NOT hot-reloaded; volume-mounted files are (with delay).

Hands-On
kubectl create configmap app-cfg --from-literal=LOG_LEVEL=debug --from-file=app.properties
kubectl get cm app-cfg -o yaml

# Mount as env
envFrom:
- configMapRef: {name: app-cfg}

# Mount as file
volumes:
- name: cfg
  configMap: {name: app-cfg}
volumeMounts:
- {name: cfg, mountPath: /etc/app}

